WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.690 --> 00:00:17.010
June 29, 2016.
2016年6月29日，

2
00:00:18.970 --> 00:00:20.822
My dear fellow citizen:
我亲爱的公民朋友们：

3
00:00:22.595 --> 00:00:24.896
I write to you today,
今天我在这向你们致辞，

4
00:00:26.213 --> 00:00:29.769
to you who have lost in this era.
献给那些迷失在这个时代中的人们。

5
00:00:31.528 --> 00:00:35.371
At this moment in our common life,
在我们平凡生活中的这个时刻，

6
00:00:35.770 --> 00:00:37.640
when the world is full of breaking
在这个充满了分裂，

7
00:00:38.245 --> 00:00:39.515
and spite
恶意，

8
00:00:40.059 --> 00:00:41.325
and fear,
和恐惧的世界，

9
00:00:43.205 --> 00:00:44.949
I address this letter
我为你

10
00:00:45.683 --> 00:00:47.464
simply to you,
写了这封信，

11
00:00:48.314 --> 00:00:49.882
even though we both know
即使我们都知道，

12
00:00:49.906 --> 00:00:54.048
there are many of you behind this "you,"
这里的“你”代表了很多的人，

13
00:00:55.126 --> 00:00:58.844
and many of me behind this "I."
这里的“我”也代表了很多人。

14
00:01:02.345 --> 00:01:04.901
I write to you because at present,
我给你们写这封信的原因，

15
00:01:06.298 --> 00:01:10.619
this quaking world we share scares me.
是我们现处的这个 不安全的世界吓到了我，

16
00:01:12.639 --> 00:01:14.630
I gather it scares you, too.
我猜它也吓到了你们。

17
00:01:16.438 --> 00:01:19.467
Some of what we fear, I suspect,
我怀疑有一些我们所恐惧的

18
00:01:19.491 --> 00:01:20.846
we fear in common.
其实是相同的。

19
00:01:21.989 --> 00:01:26.354
But much of what we fear seems to be each other.
但是我们很多的恐惧似乎源于彼此之间。

20
00:01:28.556 --> 00:01:31.476
You fear the world I want to live in,
你们害怕我想要生活的世界，

21
00:01:32.349 --> 00:01:36.237
and I fear your visions in turn.
我也害怕你们所想的那种。

22
00:01:37.493 --> 00:01:42.266
Do you know that feeling you get when you know it's going to storm
你们了解那种感觉吗？

23
00:01:40.070 --> 00:01:43.837
before it storms?
那种在暴风雨来临前的感觉？

24
00:01:45.821 --> 00:01:48.289
Do you also feel that now,
你们现在有这种感觉吗，

25
00:01:49.096 --> 00:01:50.336
fellow citizen?
我的公民朋友们？

26
00:01:52.255 --> 00:01:54.977
That malaise and worry
那种心神不安又焦虑的感觉，

27
00:01:56.001 --> 00:01:57.590
that some who know
会让你们当中的一些人

28
00:01:59.337 --> 00:02:02.003
feel reminds them of the 1930s?
想起上世纪30年代？

29
00:02:03.698 --> 00:02:05.567
Perhaps you don't,
也许你没有这种感觉，

30
00:02:06.313 --> 00:02:08.220
because our fears of each other
因为我们对彼此的恐惧

31
00:02:08.244 --> 00:02:09.763
are not in sync.
不是同步的。

32
00:02:11.145 --> 00:02:14.621
In this round, I sense that your fears of me,
在这一轮中，我感觉到了 你们对我的恐惧，

33
00:02:15.475 --> 00:02:18.827
of the world that I have insisted is right for us both,
对这个我所坚持的世界的恐惧，

34
00:02:20.676 --> 00:02:22.506
has gathered over a generation.
这些恐惧积累了超过一个时代。

35
00:02:23.837 --> 00:02:27.956
It took time for your fears to trigger my fears,
你们的恐惧需要时间 来激发我的恐惧，

36
00:02:28.688 --> 00:02:31.446
not least because at first,
因为至少在一开始，

37
00:02:31.486 --> 00:02:34.175
I never thought I needed to fear you.
我从未想过我需要惧怕你。

38
00:02:36.702 --> 00:02:38.039
I heard you
我听见了你的声音，

39
00:02:39.557 --> 00:02:40.890
but did not listen,
但是我没有仔细聆听。

40
00:02:41.551 --> 00:02:46.548
all these years when you said that this amazing new world
这些年里每当你们说起 这个令人震惊的新世界，

41
00:02:48.024 --> 00:02:49.574
wasn't amazing for you,
对于你们来说并不震惊，

42
00:02:50.699 --> 00:02:52.303
for many of you,
对于你们中很多人来说，

43
00:02:52.327 --> 00:02:54.850
across the industrialized world;
对于这个工业化的世界；

44
00:02:55.738 --> 00:02:58.559
that the open, liquid world I relished,
这个我享受的开放的、流动的世界，

45
00:02:58.583 --> 00:03:02.886
of people and goods and technologies flowing freely,
这个人力物力和科技都自由流通，

46
00:03:02.910 --> 00:03:05.350
going where they pleased, globally,
在世界范围内 去心之所向之地的时代，

47
00:03:06.839 --> 00:03:11.099
was not, for you, an emancipation.
对于你来说， 并非是一种解放。

48
00:03:13.273 --> 00:03:15.714
I have walked through your towns
当我经过你们的城镇，

49
00:03:17.262 --> 00:03:21.002
and, while looking, failed to see.
观赏时却什么也没看见。

50
00:03:22.619 --> 00:03:26.550
I did notice in Stephenville, Texas,
我在德克萨斯州 斯蒂芬威尔市注意到

51
00:03:27.611 --> 00:03:29.918
that the town square was dominated
那里的市中心广场是被

52
00:03:29.942 --> 00:03:33.185
by one lawyer's office after another,
连排的律师事务所霸占的，

53
00:03:34.214 --> 00:03:37.215
because of all the people rotating in and out of the prison.
因为那些不断进出于监狱的人们。

54
00:03:38.044 --> 00:03:42.122
I did notice the barren shops in Wagner, South Dakota,
我有注意到在南达科他州 瓦格纳市那些荒芜的商店，

55
00:03:43.745 --> 00:03:47.223
and the VFW gathering hall
和那些退伍军人的聚集场所，

56
00:03:48.134 --> 00:03:49.926
that stood in mockery
坐落于城市梦想之上，

57
00:03:50.754 --> 00:03:53.545
of a community's dream to endure.
却忍受嘲讽。

58
00:03:55.172 --> 00:03:56.386
I did notice
我有注意到

59
00:03:57.143 --> 00:04:00.568
at the Lancaster, Pennsylvania Wal-Mart,
在宾夕法尼亚州 兰开斯特市的沃尔玛超市中，

60
00:04:01.265 --> 00:04:05.624
that far too many people in their 20s and 30s
太多二三十岁的年轻人，

61
00:04:05.648 --> 00:04:08.155
looked a decade or two from death,
看起来就像与死亡只差十几二十年，

62
00:04:09.115 --> 00:04:11.461
with patchy, flared-up skin
有着色素沉积的皮肤，

63
00:04:11.485 --> 00:04:13.961
and thinning, stringy hair
稀疏散乱的头发，

64
00:04:13.985 --> 00:04:15.637
and browning, ground-down teeth
泛黄磨损的牙齿，

65
00:04:15.661 --> 00:04:18.922
and a lostness in their eyes.
和迷离的眼神。

66
00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:24.590
I did notice that the young people I encountered in Paris,
我注意到了那些在巴黎街头

67
00:04:24.614 --> 00:04:26.565
in Florence, in Barcelona,
在弗罗里达，在巴塞罗那的青年，

68
00:04:26.589 --> 00:04:30.099
had degrees but no place to take them,
身怀文凭却无处可去，

69
00:04:31.532 --> 00:04:34.496
living on internships well into their 30s,
年近30仍靠实习为生，

70
00:04:35.513 --> 00:04:38.409
their lives prevented from launching,
他们人生展翅高飞的机会被抹杀了

71
00:04:39.688 --> 00:04:42.434
because of an economy that creates wealth --
因为经济创造财富

72
00:04:43.229 --> 00:04:44.568
just not jobs.
而不是工作

73
00:04:45.656 --> 00:04:51.958
I did notice the news about those parts of London becoming ghost quarters,
我注意到了那些关于 伦敦市区空洞化的新闻，

74
00:04:52.845 --> 00:04:58.513
where the global super-rich turn fishy money into empty apartments
在那儿世界级富豪 把现钱变为空洞公寓，

75
00:04:59.782 --> 00:05:03.884
and price lifelong residents of a city, young couples starting out,
为城市定居居民定价， 年轻夫妇从这儿离开，

76
00:05:03.908 --> 00:05:05.623
out of their own home.
离开他们本来的家。

77
00:05:08.152 --> 00:05:11.073
And I heard that the fabric of your life
我听说，

78
00:05:08.997 --> 00:05:12.342
was tearing.
是眼泪编织了你们的生活。

79
00:05:13.394 --> 00:05:15.798
You used to be able to count on work,
你们曾经能指着工作过日子，

80
00:05:16.660 --> 00:05:17.989
and now you couldn't.
而现在不行了。

81
00:05:18.797 --> 00:05:21.637
You used to be able to nourish your children,
你们曾经能富养你们的孩子，

82
00:05:22.899 --> 00:05:25.240
and guarantee that they would climb
至少保证他们在人生中

83
00:05:25.872 --> 00:05:29.798
a little bit further in life than you had,
比你们自己爬得更高一些，

84
00:05:29.822 --> 00:05:31.115
and now you couldn't.
但现在不行了。

85
00:05:32.194 --> 00:05:37.779
You used to be made to feel dignity in your work, and now you didn't.
你们曾经能在工作中找到尊严，但现在不行了。

86
00:05:39.615 --> 00:05:43.011
It used to be normal for people like you to own a home,
在过去，像你们这样的人们 有个家是十分正常的事情，

87
00:05:44.290 --> 00:05:45.669
and now it wasn't.
但现在却不是这样。

88
00:05:47.106 --> 00:05:49.286
I cannot say
我不能否认

89
00:05:50.246 --> 00:05:52.037
I didn't know these things,
我很早就知道这些事，

90
00:05:53.521 --> 00:05:55.738
but I was distracted
但是我却被分了神，

91
00:05:57.389 --> 00:06:00.807
creating a future in which we could live on Mars,
去为人类在火星上的未来生活而奋斗

92
00:06:02.911 --> 00:06:06.271
even as you struggled down here on Earth.
就算你们依然在地球上艰苦的过着日子

93
00:06:07.975 --> 00:06:09.435
I was distracted
我被分了神，

94
00:06:10.275 --> 00:06:12.109
innovating immortality,
去创造永生，

95
00:06:14.339 --> 00:06:19.132
even as many of you began to live shorter lives than your parents had.
就在你们中很多人的寿命已开始 短于你们父母那代人了。

96
00:06:21.121 --> 00:06:24.180
I heard all of these things, but I didn't listen.
这些事都经过了我的耳朵， 可惜我没有去仔细倾听。

97
00:06:25.348 --> 00:06:26.547
I looked
我看了，

98
00:06:27.386 --> 00:06:28.957
but didn't see.
但是没看见。

99
00:06:28.981 --> 00:06:32.106
I read, didn't understand.
我读了，可是没理解。

100
00:06:33.190 --> 00:06:34.396
I paid attention
只有当你们去投票，去喊叫，

101
00:06:35.209 --> 00:06:39.081
only when you began to vote and shout,
只有当事情本身开始

102
00:06:40.248 --> 00:06:43.312
and when your voting and shouting, when the substance of it,
威胁到我自身的时候，

103
00:06:43.336 --> 00:06:45.819
began to threaten me.
我才会去注意到。

104
00:06:48.055 --> 00:06:53.048
I listened only when you moved toward shattering continental unions
只有当你们前往各处大陆工会，

105
00:06:53.072 --> 00:06:55.333
and electing vulgar demagogues.
当你们成为选举煽动者的时候， 我才会真正听见。

106
00:06:56.524 --> 00:07:00.428
Only then did your pain become of interest
只有到那时候，

107
00:07:01.163 --> 00:07:02.328
to me.
你们的痛苦才能被我注意。

108
00:07:04.137 --> 00:07:06.091
I know that feeling hurt
我知道感到难受

109
00:07:06.115 --> 00:07:09.408
is often prologue to dealing hurt.
经常是解决问题序幕。

110
00:07:11.484 --> 00:07:12.864
I wonder now
我在想，

111
00:07:14.228 --> 00:07:16.506
if you would be less eager to deal it
若现在我和你们身处同一战线，

112
00:07:17.258 --> 00:07:19.198
if I had stood with you
而你仅仅是感觉到了，

113
00:07:19.222 --> 00:07:21.506
when you merely felt it.
你们会因此就不想去处理它吗？

114
00:07:23.133 --> 00:07:24.410
I ask myself
我质问自己，

115
00:07:25.175 --> 00:07:27.268
why I didn't stand with you then.
为什么没有和你站在一起。

116
00:07:28.694 --> 00:07:32.071
One reason is that I became entranced
一个原因是

117
00:07:30.665 --> 00:07:34.184
by the gurus of change,
我着迷于改变，

118
00:07:35.007 --> 00:07:39.342
became a worshiper of the religion of the new for novelty's sake,
为了创新成为新新事物理念，

119
00:07:39.366 --> 00:07:41.519
and of globalization and open borders
成为全球化和开放性，

120
00:07:41.543 --> 00:07:44.480
and kaleidoscopic diversity.
成为多样性的拥护者。

121
00:07:46.748 --> 00:07:50.656
Once change became my totalizing faith,
一旦“改变”成为了我的信仰，

122
00:07:52.235 --> 00:07:53.637
I could be blind.
我就开始变得盲目。

123
00:07:54.963 --> 00:07:58.497
I could fail to see change's consequences.
我可能忽视改变带来的后果，

124
00:07:59.686 --> 00:08:01.623
I could overlook the importance
我可能忽视那些

125
00:08:01.647 --> 00:08:04.749
of roots, traditions, rituals, stability --
根源，传统，仪式，稳定性

126
00:08:04.773 --> 00:08:06.116
and belonging.
－归属感的重要性。

127
00:08:07.321 --> 00:08:10.636
And the more fundamentalist I became
当我越发变得崇拜

128
00:08:10.660 --> 00:08:14.402
in my worship of change and openness,
改变和开放，

129
00:08:15.910 --> 00:08:19.140
the more I drove you towards the other polarity,
我就越发把你们推往另一个极端，

130
00:08:19.894 --> 00:08:21.054
to cling,
那些依恋派，

131
00:08:21.452 --> 00:08:22.609
to freeze,
保守派，

132
00:08:23.097 --> 00:08:24.268
to close,
与世隔绝的，

133
00:08:24.920 --> 00:08:26.079
to belong.
或是归属思想。

134
00:08:27.958 --> 00:08:30.674
I now see as I didn't before
我现在比以往看见更多，

135
00:08:30.698 --> 00:08:34.639
that not having the right skin or right organ
没有优越的皮肤和器官，

136
00:08:34.663 --> 00:08:38.586
is not the only varietal of disadvantage.
并不是百害而无一利。

137
00:08:39.542 --> 00:08:43.132
There is a subtler, quieter disadvantage
对于拥有优势特质的那些皮肤器官，

138
00:08:43.156 --> 00:08:46.471
in having those privileged traits
存在一个更加细微，潜在的危险。

139
00:08:46.495 --> 00:08:50.878
and yet feeling history to be moving away from you;
当认为历史在离你而去，

140
00:08:50.902 --> 00:08:54.295
that while the past was hospitable to people like you,
对像你们这样的人有害的历史，

141
00:08:54.319 --> 00:08:56.717
the future will be more hospitable
也许对另一些人，

142
00:08:56.741 --> 00:08:58.134
to others;
未来则更加险恶；

143
00:08:58.158 --> 00:09:00.611
that the world is growing less familiar,
与你们记忆中的相比，

144
00:09:00.635 --> 00:09:03.501
less yours day by day.
世界一天天变得更加生疏。

145
00:09:05.685 --> 00:09:11.367
I will not concede for a moment that old privileges should not dwindle.
我当然不会承认旧权不该被缩减。

146
00:09:11.875 --> 00:09:14.621
They cannot dwindle fast enough.
它们缩减的速度还远远不够。

147
00:09:15.605 --> 00:09:19.105
It is for you to learn to live in a new century in which
你们应该明白在新的历史时代里，

148
00:09:19.130 --> 00:09:23.954
there are no bonuses for showing up with the right skin and right organs.
与生俱来的优势皮肤和器官 不会带来什么奖励。

149
00:09:25.097 --> 00:09:27.524
If and when your anger turns to hate,
如果当你的气愤转化为痛恨，

150
00:09:27.549 --> 00:09:31.779
please know that there is no space for that in our shared home.
请明白在我们共享的家园里 没有容纳那些痛恨的空间。

151
00:09:33.462 --> 00:09:36.810
But I will admit, fellow citizen,
但我会承认，我的朋友们，

152
00:09:37.960 --> 00:09:43.499
that I have discounted the burden of coping with the loss of status.
我忽视了应对地位丧失的压力。

153
00:09:43.983 --> 00:09:45.752
I have forgotten
我忘却了

154
00:09:45.777 --> 00:09:50.522
that what is socially necessary can also be personally gruelling.
那些社会必须的也会成为个人折磨。

155
00:09:52.739 --> 00:09:54.244
A similar thing happened
对于你我共享的经济体，

156
00:09:55.037 --> 00:09:58.661
with the economy that you and I share.
相似地事发生了。

157
00:10:00.011 --> 00:10:02.443
Just as I cannot and don't wish
正如我不能，也不愿

158
00:10:02.467 --> 00:10:06.094
to turn back to the clock on equality and diversity,
背视那平等与多样性的时钟，

159
00:10:06.118 --> 00:10:08.447
and yet must understand
但必须明白

160
00:10:08.471 --> 00:10:11.237
the sense of loss they can inspire,
它们能够激励的那种失去感，

161
00:10:12.847 --> 00:10:17.005
so, too, I refuse and could not if I wished
因此，我拒绝，也不能够去

162
00:10:17.790 --> 00:10:21.931
turn back the clock on an ever more closely knit, interdependent world,
希望时光倒流回相互联系，依赖的世界之前

163
00:10:21.955 --> 00:10:25.345
and on inventions that won't stop being invented.
回到发明不断之前。

164
00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:31.574
And yet I must understand your experience of these things.
但我也必须意识到 你们所经历的这些。

165
00:10:32.852 --> 00:10:36.271
You have for years been telling me that your experience of these things
你们多年来都在诉说 你们经历过的这些种种

166
00:10:36.295 --> 00:10:39.437
is not as good as my theories forecast.
并不向我理论预测中的那么美好。

167
00:10:40.348 --> 00:10:44.206
Yet before you could finish a complaining sentence
但在你们能够诉说完

168
00:10:45.936 --> 00:10:51.424
about the difficulty of living with erratic hours, volatile pay,
关于生活的艰辛， 异常的时间，蒸发的工资，

169
00:10:51.448 --> 00:10:53.074
vanishing opportunities,
消失的机会，

170
00:10:53.098 --> 00:10:57.356
about the pain of dropping your children off at 24-hour day care
关于将孩子寄托给全天托管班

171
00:10:57.380 --> 00:10:59.143
to make your 3am shift,
为了完成凌晨3点的 工作换班的痛苦之前，

172
00:11:00.139 --> 00:11:04.052
I shot back at you -- before you could finish your sentence --
我就用我的信条－在你们完成诉说之前－

173
00:11:04.076 --> 00:11:05.418
my dogma,
驳回你们，

174
00:11:05.442 --> 00:11:09.872
about how what you are actually experiencing was flexibility
告诉你们其实你们经历的

175
00:11:10.614 --> 00:11:11.900
and freedom.
是灵活和自由。

176
00:11:14.411 --> 00:11:18.982
Language is one of the only things that we truly share,
语言是我们真正共有的 唯几样事物之一，

177
00:11:20.369 --> 00:11:23.848
and I sometimes used this joint inheritance
而我有时候却用这共同的遗产，

178
00:11:23.872 --> 00:11:25.083
to obfuscate
去混淆，

179
00:11:25.641 --> 00:11:26.845
and deflect
去转移，

180
00:11:27.299 --> 00:11:28.815
and justify myself;
去为自己辩护；

181
00:11:29.753 --> 00:11:31.633
to re-brand what was good for me
当我抛出例如“共同经济”

182
00:11:31.657 --> 00:11:34.449
as something appearing good for us both,
“混乱”

183
00:11:35.144 --> 00:11:39.130
when I threw around terms like "the sharing economy,"
“共享经济”这样短语的时候，

184
00:11:39.955 --> 00:11:41.130
and "disruption"
去重新辩解对自身有力的，

185
00:11:41.665 --> 00:11:43.510
and "global resourcing."
其实是对大家都有利的。

186
00:11:45.044 --> 00:11:47.415
I see now that what I was really doing,
我意识到我有时

187
00:11:48.049 --> 00:11:49.295
at times,
真正在从事的，

188
00:11:49.714 --> 00:11:52.818
was buying your pain on the cheap,
是廉价买下你们的痛苦，

189
00:11:53.712 --> 00:11:54.924
sprucing it up
稍微改进一下，

190
00:11:55.592 --> 00:11:57.564
and trying to sell it back to you
然后尝试重新卖给你们

191
00:11:58.064 --> 00:11:59.270
as freedom.
凭借自由的旗号。

192
00:12:01.532 --> 00:12:04.791
I have wanted to believe and wanted you to believe
我希望去相信，也希望你们去相信，

193
00:12:07.503 --> 00:12:09.612
that the system that has been good to me,
那对我适用的体系，

194
00:12:09.636 --> 00:12:12.309
that has made my life ever more seamless,
让我的人生天衣无缝的体系，

195
00:12:13.049 --> 00:12:15.944
is also the best system for you.
也是最适合你们的体系。

196
00:12:17.364 --> 00:12:19.625
I have condescended to you
我自带优越感地向你们灌输观点：

197
00:12:19.649 --> 00:12:23.545
with the idea that you are voting against your economic interests --
你们是在对经济利益投反对票－

198
00:12:24.027 --> 00:12:25.815
voting against your interests,
对你们自身的利益投反对票，

199
00:12:27.441 --> 00:12:30.664
as if I know your interests.
仿佛我知道你们利益的样子。

200
00:12:32.116 --> 00:12:36.433
That is just my dogmatic economism talking.
这只是我自身教条的经济论。

201
00:12:37.543 --> 00:12:39.320
I have a weakness
我有这样一个问题，

202
00:12:39.344 --> 00:12:44.729
for treating people's economic interests as their only interest,
就是总把经济利益 看作所有人的唯一利益。

203
00:12:44.753 --> 00:12:48.277
ignoring things like belonging and pride
忽视了那些归属感，骄傲情绪，

204
00:12:48.301 --> 00:12:52.075
and the desire to send a message to those who ignore you.
和对于那些忽视你的人们 发出信息的欲望。

205
00:12:52.508 --> 00:12:55.239
So here we are,
我们就是这样，

206
00:12:56.063 --> 00:13:00.689
in a scary but not inexplicable moment
身处一个可怕但并非莫名奇妙的

207
00:13:01.327 --> 00:13:03.650
of demagoguery, fracture,
躁动的，受挫的，

208
00:13:04.301 --> 00:13:08.187
xenophobia, resentment and fear.
排外的，痛恨的，惧怕的时刻。

209
00:13:09.448 --> 00:13:13.478
And I worry for us both if we continue down this road,
如果我们继续这条道路：

210
00:13:14.178 --> 00:13:15.574
me not listening,
我不听，你感觉没被倾听，

211
00:13:16.125 --> 00:13:17.976
you feeling unheard,
你为了让我听而喊叫。

212
00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:20.549
you shouting to get me to listen.
我将为你我感到担心。

213
00:13:22.599 --> 00:13:26.050
I worry when each of us is seduced by visions of the future
我担心我们中的每一个人都会被

214
00:13:26.074 --> 00:13:28.734
that have no place for the other.
不给别人留出路 的未来景象所诱惑。

215
00:13:29.551 --> 00:13:31.639
If this goes on,
如果这继续下去，

216
00:13:33.475 --> 00:13:34.850
if this goes on,
继续这样下去，

217
00:13:35.873 --> 00:13:37.352
there may be blood.
可能会演变为血案。

218
00:13:39.110 --> 00:13:41.795
There are already hints of this blood
在每天的报纸当中，

219
00:13:42.735 --> 00:13:44.075
in newspapers every day.
已经有一些血案前兆了。

220
00:13:44.787 --> 00:13:47.372
There may be roundups, raids,
可能会出现混乱，暴动，

221
00:13:47.406 --> 00:13:50.481
deportations, camps, secessions.
搜捕，驱逐营，分裂。

222
00:13:51.314 --> 00:13:54.235
And no, I do not think that I exaggerate.
不，我不是在虚张声势。

223
00:13:56.056 --> 00:13:57.977
There may be even talk of war
有可能会有战争，

224
00:13:58.001 --> 00:14:01.551
in places that were certain they were done with it.
出现在口口声声认同 已不会有战争的地方。

225
00:14:03.303 --> 00:14:07.049
There is always the hope of redemption.
一直以来都有补救的希望。

226
00:14:07.584 --> 00:14:10.862
But it will not be a cheap, shallow redemption
但这并非是一个廉价的， 浅显易得的救赎

227
00:14:10.886 --> 00:14:14.557
that comes through blather about us all being in it together.
不仅仅是嘴上说说我们团结一致。

228
00:14:15.132 --> 00:14:16.988
This will take more.
这会需要更多。

229
00:14:18.216 --> 00:14:23.408
It will take accepting that we both made choices to be here.
我们需要承认我们选择在这儿。

230
00:14:25.683 --> 00:14:28.786
We create our "others."
是我们创造了“其他人”的概念。

231
00:14:29.795 --> 00:14:33.475
As parents, as neighbors, as citizens,
作为家长，邻居，公民，

232
00:14:34.323 --> 00:14:38.654
we witness and sometimes ignore each other
我们见证，

233
00:14:38.678 --> 00:14:39.918
into being.
有时也忽视他人的存在。

234
00:14:41.088 --> 00:14:44.138
You were not born vengeful.
我们并非生来就复仇心切。

235
00:14:45.159 --> 00:14:47.166
I have some role
我也饰演一些角色，

236
00:14:47.190 --> 00:14:50.691
in whatever thirst you now feel for revenge,
无论你现在是多么渴望复仇，

237
00:14:51.505 --> 00:14:53.418
and that thirst now tempts me
那些复仇的渴望感诱使我

238
00:14:53.442 --> 00:14:55.960
to plot ever more elaborate escapes
设计前所未有精密的路线，

239
00:14:55.984 --> 00:14:57.903
from our common life,
去逃离我们共同生活，

240
00:14:57.927 --> 00:14:59.796
from the schools and neighborhoods
逃离学校和邻里，

241
00:14:59.820 --> 00:15:01.751
and airports and amusement parks
逃离机场和游乐场，

242
00:15:01.775 --> 00:15:03.416
that we used to share.
逃离那些我们曾经共有的地方。

243
00:15:05.479 --> 00:15:08.467
We face, then,
之后，我们面对的

244
00:15:08.491 --> 00:15:12.265
a problem not of these large, impersonal forces.
不是那些远大的非个人的问题，

245
00:15:14.186 --> 00:15:18.338
We face a problem of your and my relations.
我们面对的是你我的关系问题。

246
00:15:19.635 --> 00:15:22.773
We chose ways of relating to each other
我们选择了相互关联的方式，

247
00:15:24.165 --> 00:15:25.316
that got us here.
让我们走到了今天这地步。

248
00:15:25.716 --> 00:15:28.465
We can choose ways of relating
我们也可以选择相互关联的方式，

249
00:15:28.489 --> 00:15:30.095
that get us out.
让我们脱离这里。

250
00:15:31.181 --> 00:15:34.450
But there are things we might have to let go of,
但我们必须放弃一些，

251
00:15:35.238 --> 00:15:36.419
fellow citizen,
我亲爱的公民伙伴们，

252
00:15:37.494 --> 00:15:43.100
starting with our own cherished versions of reality.
首先是我们自身珍视的现实视角。

253
00:15:44.855 --> 00:15:48.724
Imagine if you let go of fantasies
想像你们放弃那些对

254
00:15:48.748 --> 00:15:52.606
of a society purged of these or those people.
没有这样或那样人的社会的幻想。

255
00:15:53.381 --> 00:15:57.034
Imagine if I let go of my habit
想像我放弃

256
00:15:57.575 --> 00:16:00.645
of saving the world behind your back,
在你们背后拯救世界的习惯，

257
00:16:01.653 --> 00:16:03.050
of deliberating on the future
想像去放弃对在连安保都无法通过地方

258
00:16:03.074 --> 00:16:04.549
of your work,
你未来的工作，

259
00:16:05.080 --> 00:16:06.326
your food,
食物，

260
00:16:06.350 --> 00:16:07.820
your schools,
学校

261
00:16:07.844 --> 00:16:10.854
in places where you couldn't get past security.
的幻想。

262
00:16:12.206 --> 00:16:16.552
We can do this only if we first accept
我们只有先承认我们忽视了彼此，

263
00:16:17.167 --> 00:16:19.810
that we have neglected each other.
才可能做到这一点。

264
00:16:21.791 --> 00:16:25.005
If there is hope to summon
如果在这不详的时刻，

265
00:16:25.750 --> 00:16:27.100
in this ominous hour,
有重新振作精神的希望，

266
00:16:28.022 --> 00:16:29.213
it is this.
那就是这个。

267
00:16:30.690 --> 00:16:32.392
We have, for too long,
我们已经太久

268
00:16:33.367 --> 00:16:36.736
chased various shimmering dreams
追寻各种闪亮的梦想，

269
00:16:37.638 --> 00:16:43.502
at the cost of attention to the foundational dream of each other,
以最基本的对你我之间梦想 的注意力为代价，

270
00:16:44.921 --> 00:16:47.489
the dream of tending to each other,
照顾彼此的梦想，

271
00:16:47.513 --> 00:16:50.376
of unleashing each other's wonders,
释放彼此疑虑的梦想，

272
00:16:50.400 --> 00:16:52.945
of moving through history together.
共同跨越历史的梦想。

273
00:16:53.866 --> 00:16:58.135
We could dare to commit to the dream of each other
我们应该敢于承认对于彼此的梦想，

274
00:16:58.829 --> 00:17:03.536
as the thing that matters before every neon thing.
承认它比其他各色事情更重要。

275
00:17:04.296 --> 00:17:05.778
Let us dare.
让我们敢于这么做。

276
00:17:06.287 --> 00:17:07.447
Sincerely yours,
敬上，

277
00:17:07.887 --> 00:17:09.063
a fellow citizen.
一个公民伙伴。

278
00:17:09.503 --> 00:17:15.128
(Applause)
（掌声）